    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    ActiveActor
    Represents an active actor in the game.
    ActiveActorDestructible
    Represents a destructible active actor in the game.
    Asteroid
    Represents an asteroid in the game.
    Boss
    Represents the boss enemy in the game.
    BossHealth
    Represents the health display for the boss in the game.
    BossProjectile
    Represents a projectile fired by the boss in the game.
    CollisionHandler
    Singleton class for handling collision detection and resolution between game entities.
    Controller
     
    Destructible
    Interface representing destructible objects in the game.
    EnemyPlane
    Represents an enemy plane in the game.
    EnemyProjectile
    Represents a projectile fired by an enemy plane in the game.
    EventListener
    Represents a listener that reacts to specific game events.
    EventNotifier
    Provides a mechanism for notifying listeners about game events.
    FighterPlane
    Represents a fighter plane in the game.
    FireRatePowerUp
    Represents a power-up that increases the fire rate of the user's plane.
    GameEvent
    Represents a game event that can occur during gameplay.
    GameEvent.EventType
     
    GameOverImage
     
    HealthPowerUp
    The HealthPowerUp class represents a power-up that increases the health of the user's plane when collected during the game.
    HeartDisplay
    The HeartDisplay class is responsible for displaying a collection of heart-shaped images in a horizontal layout, represented by an HBox container.
    LevelFour
    Represents the fourth level of the game.
    LevelFourView
    This class represents the view for the fourth level.
    LevelOne
    Represents the first level of the game.
    LevelParent
    Base class for all levels in the game.
    LevelThree
    Represents the third level of the game.
    LevelTwo
    Represents the second level of the game.
    LevelView
    Represents the view for a game level.
    LevelViewLevelTwo
    Represents the view for LevelTwo.
    LevelViewThree
    Represents the view for LevelThree.
    Main
    The main entry point for the Sky Battle game application.
    MainMenu
    Represents the main menu of the game.
    PowerUp
    Represents a power-up in the game.
    Projectile
    Represents a projectile in the game.
    ShieldImage
    Represents a shield image in the game.
    UserPlane
    Represents the player's plane in the game.
    UserProjectile
    Represents a projectile fired by the player.
    WinImage
    Represents the win image displayed at the end of the game.
